cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC 

This paper deals with automatic kinship verification using facial images, which is a problem in computer vision. The paper explores the use of both shallow texture features and deep features for characterizing faces, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and the machine learning sub-category. The paper also involves extensive experiments, which could suggest that it could belong to the learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of facial dynamics in kinship verification could suggest that it could belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of videos in addition to still images could suggest that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
